3. Article 3 of the Principal Regulations is amended by the insertion of - 

““Act of 2024” means the Local Government (Mayor of Limerick) and 
Miscellaneous Provisions Act 2024; 

“Limerick City and County Council” shall be construed as in accordance with 
subsection (3) of section 11 of, and Part 3 of Schedule 5 to, the Local 
Government Act 2001; 

“Mayor” has the meaning assigned to it by section 9 of the Act of 2024; 

“Príomh Comhairleoir” has the meaning assigned to it by section 22 of the Act 
of 2024; 

“director general” has the meaning assigned to it by section 26 of the Act of 
2024; 

“Cathaoirleach” shall, in the case of Limerick City and County Council, be read 
as “Príomh Comhairleoir”; 

“Chief Executive” shall, in the case of Limerick City and County Council, be 
read as “director general”.” 

Notice of the making of this Statutory Instrument was published in 
"Iris Oifigiúil" of 31st May, 2024. 








 [256] 3 

Amendment of Article4 of Principal Regulations
